http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/Seminar-stresses-formation-of-social-capital/article13999013.ece

The National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development (NABARD) has assessed that credit potential under priority sector would be Rs. 1.21 lakh crore for the year 2016-17 in its State focus paper 2016-17. The State focus0 paper maps the sectoral credit potential, infrastructural constraints and issues required by the State government and bankers to support the credit potential.The focus paper was released at a seminar on state credit organised by Nabard here on Wednesday.The speakers at the seminar stressed on the need for qualitative lending rather than quantitative lending. Mere statistical reviews would not suffice.